Player stats (optional): /pub/player/{username}/stats : Returns rating summaries
across game types. You may use this to construct pre-game features if you
find it useful.
What to Build
Data collection and feature engineering
Using the tournament data, construct a dataset where each row
represents a single game. Your goal is to predict the outcome of the game
(win / loss / draw from White’s perspective). The API returns several fields
per game; not all of them are appropriate as input features.
Model
Train a model to predict the game outcome. We’re not looking for a
leaderboard-topping solution. Instead, we want to see how you frame the
problem, what tradeoffs you make, and how you evaluate performance. A
simple and well-reasoned model with clear evaluation is better for this
exercise than a complex model with unclear metrics.
